The paper focuses on the problem of selecting representative samples from phenomena with periodic structure, which is a common problem in robotics and environmental monitoring domains. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel sample selection algorithm that recovers a near-optimal sample set according to any monotone submodular utility function, which is related to machine learning and optimization, and thus cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper evaluates the algorithm on a dataset collected at the Martha's Vineyard Coastal Observatory, which involves image processing and computer vision, and thus cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the applications of the proposed algorithm in real-time sensing and robotics, which is related to systems and control, and thus cs.SI (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category.
